From the overall rating of 3.8 on google at the time of writing this review, I feel this place is so under-rated. I had a wonderful time here and this place deserves a better rating than mere 3.8. The taste of the food is at par with other restaurants in the area and is definitely one of the best amongst the indian restaurants I have tried in chicago at this price point. I recommend their thali as it offers a variety of items and is enough to feed 1.5 normally hungry individuals or maybe 1 very very hungry person. Most of their dishes are low on salt but I guess it's to suit the variety of different clients that come. It's always better to keep it low and then add later as needed.  The first look of this restaurant does look a bit shady and unappealing from the outside but I frankly loved the ambience inside the restaurant.  The staff was courteous and made all possible efforts to serve us the best they can during these unprecedented times.  Overall, I would highly recommend this place if you are near mag mile and want to eat indian food.

Located across the street from the 900 North Michigan shops on the Walton Street offshoot, Gaylord find Indian cuisine is one of the premier Indian restaurants in the city of Chicago. While consumers of authentic Indian food usually gravitate towards the Devon Street neighborhood near Rogers Park, interested patrons that enjoy South Indian cuisine should consider Gaylord find Indian cuisine as being of a similar tier to the restaurants in the Devon Street area. The added benefit of Gaylord finr Indian cuisine is that a person need not venture to Rogers Park. This reviewer in particular would recommend the lunch buffet menu which for $16 allows a customer to eat substantial portion including but not limited to saag paneer, naan bread, tandoori chicken, and basmati rice.

And while trying the amex again he tells me some times if people tip to much it gives error being sarcastic and said the lady paid 50$ tip on 22$ bill. And then we had tipped 3$ as there was no need of service from them as it was a buffet and he says 44$ bill and 3$ tip also does not work. Thinking about his age I did not feel like insulting him but this is not the way you talk. If you would have been out of your way to serve me I also would have done the same. For Father's day I wanted to take my Husband out for Indian food. I've been coming to Gaylord since the 1st Location on Clark st, but I haven't gone in years. I Google the Location & to my surprise I saw a lot of reviews from recent visits that were rated horribly. So I called.  I spoke with Mr. Pasawala himself & expressed to him that I saw all of the bad reviews. He simply told me not to believe them. He said that all kinds of people- including other Indian business owners will post anything to gain more Customers.  I trusted what he said & went today with another couple. THE FOOD WAS AMAZINGLY AWESOME!!!!! THE SERVER & SERVICE WERE EXTREMELY PROFESSIONAL!  If you're like me, you know that Good reviews are what makes a business thrive. The bad ones almost kept me away. Overall I'm glad I followed my heart & my stomach 😊  THANK YOU ALL FOR A TERRIFIC FATHER'S DAY DINNER🙏

I would seriously suggest avoid going to the same.
